abstract: The average U.S. price of regular-grade gasoline has dipped 4 cents per gallon to $2.61 over the past two weeks.
snippet: The average U.S. price of regular-grade gasoline has dipped 4 cents per gallon to $2.61 over the past two weeks.
lead_paragraph: CAMARILLO, Calif. — The average U.S. price of regular-grade gasoline has dipped 4 cents per gallon to $2.61 over the past two weeks.
headline_main: Gas Prices Drop 4 Cents Per Gallon to $2.61
headline_print_headline: Gas Prices Drop 4 Cents Per Gallon to $2.61

abstract: Egypt, Ethiopia and Sudan have come closer to aligning their views on filling the reservoir of and operating the giant hydroelectric dam that Ethiopia is building on the Blue Nile, the Sudanese irrigation minister said on Sunday.
snippet: Egypt, Ethiopia and Sudan have come closer to aligning their views on filling the reservoir of and operating the giant hydroelectric dam that Ethiopia is building on the Blue Nile, the Sudanese irrigation minister said on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: KHARTOUM — Egypt, Ethiopia and Sudan have come closer to aligning their views on filling the reservoir of and operating the giant hydroelectric dam that Ethiopia is building on the Blue Nile, the Sudanese irrigation minister said on Sunday.
headline_main: Egypt, Ethiopia, Sudan Views Come Closer on Giant Nile Dam-Sudanese Minister
headline_print_headline: Egypt, Ethiopia, Sudan Views Come Closer on Giant Nile Dam-Sudanese Minister

abstract: The Egyptian military on Sunday released one of the country's former chiefs-of-staff, nearly two years after his arrest following an announcement that he would challenge President Abdel-Fattah el-Sissi in the 2018 presidential vote, military officials and his lawyer said.
snippet: The Egyptian military on Sunday released one of the country's former chiefs-of-staff, nearly two years after his arrest following an announcement that he would challenge President Abdel-Fattah el-Sissi in the 2018 presidential vote, military offic...
lead_paragraph: CAIRO — The Egyptian military on Sunday released one of the country's former chiefs-of-staff, nearly two years after his arrest following an announcement that he would challenge President Abdel-Fattah el-Sissi in the 2018 presidential vote, military officials and his lawyer said.
headline_main: Egypt Frees Ex-General Arrested After Challenging President
headline_print_headline: Egypt Frees Ex-General Arrested After Challenging President

abstract: Chelsea enjoyed a timely return to form to outplay Tottenham Hotspur in a 2-0 away victory in the Premier League as Frank Lampard outwitted his former mentor Jose Mourinho in their managerial battle on Sunday.
snippet: Chelsea enjoyed a timely return to form to outplay Tottenham Hotspur in a 2-0 away victory in the Premier League as Frank Lampard outwitted his former mentor Jose Mourinho in their managerial battle on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Chelsea enjoyed a timely return to form to outplay Tottenham Hotspur in a 2-0 away victory in the Premier League as Frank Lampard outwitted his former mentor Jose Mourinho in their managerial battle on Sunday.
headline_main: Chelsea Outplay Tottenham With Willian Double
headline_print_headline: Chelsea Outplay Tottenham With Willian Double

abstract: Dating to 1812, the lottery has become a major part of Spain’s festive calendar, developing an array of traditions.
snippet: Dating to 1812, the lottery has become a major part of Spain’s festive calendar, developing an array of traditions.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — As a crowd gathered at Doña Manolita, a stall in central Madrid that has been selling tickets to the lottery known as El Gordo for over 100 years, employees popped bottles of cava. They had sold a winner.

abstract: A series of winter storms unleashed heavy rain and strong winds across Portugal, Spain, France and Britain.
snippet: A series of winter storms unleashed heavy rain and strong winds across Portugal, Spain, France and Britain.
lead_paragraph: VIGO, Spain — A one-two punch of winter storms has socked Europe with strong winds and rain over several days, leaving at least nine people dead.

abstract: In this Bollywood action flick, Salman Khan is a one-man wrecking crew. When not knocking heads, he dances.
snippet: In this Bollywood action flick, Salman Khan is a one-man wrecking crew. When not knocking heads, he dances.
lead_paragraph: The Bollywood movie “Dabangg 3” opens with several bangs: Wedding robbers are doing what wedding robbers do — collecting guests’ gold chunks and cash — when the police arrive on the scene. The officers bumble until their leader, our hero, Inspector Chulbul Pandey, blasts his way onto the scene. He comes flying through a wall, riding what looks to be a giant drill (or is it a modest rocket?) and proceeds to punch, karate chop, kick, toss in the air, and generally drub the miscreants in a way that would be purely cartoonish if not for a dose of mild sadism. (Crotch, meet knife.)

abstract: A Los Angeles church is paying off $5.3 million worth of medical debt for nearly 6,000 households in Southern California, according to one of the church's pastors.
